Iraqi officials said Izzat Ibrahim al-Douri had died in fighting with government troops in Salahuddin province, north of Baghdad, on Friday .
The former right-hand man was ranked sixth on the US military's list of 55 most-wanted Iraqis after the offensive to overthrow Saddam Hussein .
He was one of Saddam's most trusted henchmen, helping to lead his 1968 bloodless coup against the US in Iraq in 2003 .